enableUA

public static final boolean enableUA
Enables or Disables calls to Urban Airship method. This variable is used for debugging the SDK only, and is set to TRUE for all release builds.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

pushEnabled

public static boolean pushEnabled
Deprecated. No longer used for managing push state. Now using a persistent store. Use isPushEnabled() in conjunction with enablePush() and disablePush() instead.
Controls state of Push with regards to user preference. Initially is set to false, but will be turned on when enablePush() is called.

pushManager

public static ETPush pushManager()

configureSDKWithAppIdAndClientIdAndClientSecret

@Deprecated
public void configureSDKWithAppIdAndClientIdAndClientSecret(java.lang.String etAppId,
                                                                       java.lang.String clientId,
                                                                       java.lang.String clientSecret)
Deprecated. Use configureSDKWithAppIdAndAccessToken() instead.

Configures the SDK to point to the correct Code@ application.

These credentials are provided by Code@ExactTarget, and are generated there. Best practice is to create two applications, one for a dev instance, and one for prod.

Parameters:
etAppId - Generated application ID to identify with ExactTarget
clientId - Generated client ID used to authenticate against Fuel
clientSecret - Generated client Secret used to authenticate against Fuel

configureSDKWithAppIdAndAccessToken

public void configureSDKWithAppIdAndAccessToken(java.lang.String etAppId,
                                                java.lang.String accessToken)
Configures the SDK to point to the correct Code@ application.

These credentials are provided by Code@ExactTarget, and are generated there. Best practice is to create two applications, one for a dev instance, and one for prod.

Parameters:
etAppId - Generated application ID to identify with ExactTarget
accessToken - Generated token to allow access to the Fuel API

registerForRemoteNotifications

public void registerForRemoteNotifications()
Wrapper method that begins the registration flow with Google/GCM.

This method requires information set by configureSDKWithAppIdAndClientIdAndClientSecret(String, String, String) and should never be called prior to that method.

unregisterForRemoteNotifications

public void unregisterForRemoteNotifications()
Wrapper method that will unregister the device with Google/GCM.

sendAppAnalytics

public void sendAppAnalytics(int secondsInApp,
                             java.lang.String messageID)
Specialized call to send back analytic data to ExactTarget and reset variables correctly.

This method should not be called by developers.

Parameters:
secondsInApp - Length of time user spent with application in the foreground, in seconds.
messageID - Optional, the message ID that prompted the application session.

isPushEnabled

public boolean isPushEnabled()
Checks persistent preferences for the state of Push. Push is enabled by either enablePush() or disablePush(), and the SDK ships with Push disabled by default. Best practice dictates that the user gathers opt-in and explicitly enables Push.

Returns:
boolean The state of push, either on or off, as managed by the Push Manager.

enablePush

public void enablePush()
Enables push and push accessories in the SDK.

This method should be called when explicit permission for Push has been given by the user. No interface for this is provided. By comparison, iOS will prompt the user when an app wants to send Push notifications. As Android doesn't, you must do so on your own.

See Also:
disablePush()

disablePush

public void disablePush()
Disables push and push accessories in the SDK.

This method should be called if the user decided they no longer wish to receive Push notifications. To be compliant, you need to provide the user with means to disable Push.

See Also:
enablePush()

updateET

Used to begin communications with ExactTarget. This method should not be called by developers, and is used internally only.

addAtributeNamedValue

public void addAtributeNamedValue(java.lang.String attribute,
                                  java.lang.String value)
Adds an attribute to current user's Contact model.

This data is available in MobilePush, and will automatically map to any matching attribute within MobilePush/Contacts.

Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided.

Parameters:
attribute - Attribute name
value - Value to assign to that attribute for this user

removeAttributeNamed

public void removeAttributeNamed(java.lang.String attribute)
Removes an attribute from the current user's data, and prevents it from being sent to ExactTarget. This will also cause that attribute to be cleared in Contacts.

Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided.

Parameters:
attribute - Name of the attribute to remove.

addTag

public void addTag(java.lang.String tag)
Adds a tag to the current user's Contact model.

This data will be available through MobilePush for use of creation of an audience.

Parameters:
tag - Name of the tag to be set

removeTag

public void removeTag(java.lang.String tag)
Removes a tag from the current user's Contact model.

Parameters:
tag - Name of the tag to remove

registerDeviceToken

public void registerDeviceToken(java.lang.String deviceToken)
Returns the device's platform-specific token to ExactTarget. This method should only be called internally by ET_GenericReceiver.onReceive(Context, android.content.Intent).

Parameters:
deviceToken - Platform-specific device token. In this case, GCM.

unregisterDeviceToken

public void unregisterDeviceToken()
Removes the device token from the user's data, effectively unregistering them from pushes.

setEmailAddress

public void setEmailAddress(java.lang.String email)
Sets the email attribute to the provided value. Pass null or an empty string to clear.

This must be captured on your own, and you should *not* query the Accounts service to retrieve the email address. All ExactTarget rules for collecting subscribers information applies here.

Parameters:
email - User's email address.
